    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-02-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-02-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="273"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d273">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">110.11 DU/2–553</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">President</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d273fn1">This message was transmitted to, the Department of
                        State in telegram 3642 from Bonn, Feb. 5, with instructions that it be
                        delivered to the President and that there should be no distribution except
                        to the Acting Secretary of State. A memorandum by <persName
                            corresp="#p_MATTHEWSHF1">Matthews</persName> attached to the source text
                        indicates that the message was delivered to the White House on Feb.
                        5.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bonn</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-02-05">February 5,
                            1953</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[<hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. President</hi>:] Our visit in London was highly
                    satisfactory so far as establishing cordial relations with UK Government and we
                    believe it will help allay public distrust re Formosa largely stirred up by
                    Labor Party and sensationalist press. Labor Party will try to exploit Formosa
                    issue to maximum as part of opposition tactics. Our visit and <persName
                        corresp="#p_EDENSA1">Eden</persName>’s statement<note n="2" xml:id="d273fn2"
                        >In telegram 4296 from London, Feb. 4, <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1"
                            >Dulles</persName> sent the Department of State a statement which
                            <persName corresp="#p_EDENSA1">Eden</persName> proposed to make in the
                        Commons concerning references in President <persName
                            corresp="#p_EISENHOWER1">Eisenhower</persName>’s State of the Union
                        message relating to policy toward Communist China. <persName
                            corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">Dulles</persName> asked if President <persName
                            corresp="#p_EISENHOWER1">Eisenhower</persName> had any objections to the
                        proposed statement. (711.5890/2–453)</note> will greatly strengthen hand of
                    government in today’s parliamentary debates.</p>
                <pb facs="0500" n="1568" xml:id="pg_1568"/>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_STASSENHE1">Stassen</persName> and I had cordial luncheon
                    with <persName corresp="#p_CHURCHILLWS1">Churchill</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_EDENSA1">Eden</persName> and the talks at Foreign Office which
                    preceded and followed developed unity of purpose re <gloss target="#t_EDC1"
                        >EDC</gloss> which the government now clearly accepts as indispensable.<note
                        n="3" xml:id="d273fn3">For a record of <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1"
                            >Dulles</persName>’ and <persName corresp="#p_STASSENHE1"
                            >Stassen</persName>’s meetings with British officials during the morning
                        and afternoon of Feb. 4, see telegram 3654 from Bonn, Feb. 5, <hi
                            rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> Several avenues of coordinated action
                    were developed.</p>
                <p>Discussions also covered Egypt, Iran, Formosa and economic matters all in an
                    atmosphere of complete confidence.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_EDENSA1">Eden</persName>’s dinner for us last night served
                    to further cement personal relations.</p>
                <p>[Best regards,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Foster</hi>
                        </persName>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
